Current behavior is extra invalid space is added to command line args in start-process

C++ code below demonstrates how \x20 is added to end of start-process -filepath C:\blah.exe -args Demo

Demo command line will have space added...  Joel and romero126 and jborean93 in the #powershell IRC chat on freenode have observed the issue.

The expected behavior is that the command line should be exactly what the person typed, no extra space at the end.  Extra spaces will break software where need exact params as cmd args (my tool stopped working randomly and I didn't know why-- spaces are an invalid input in the software I made)

powershell version:

